  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is correct. The average time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\"><mi>t</mi></math>, in minutes, it takes Carly to travel a certain distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\"><mi>d</mi></math>, in kilometers, is given in the table. This linear relationship can be represented by an equation in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t equals a d plus b\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\"><mi>a</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math> are constants. The table shows that it takes Carly an average time of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn></math> minutes to travel <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.32\"><mn>0.32</mn></math> kilometers. Substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\"><mi>t</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.32\"><mn>0.32</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\"><mi>d</mi></math> in the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t equals a d plus b\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8 equals 0.32 a plus b\"><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0.32</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>. Subtracting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.32 a\"><mn>0.32</mn><mi>a</mi></math> from both sides of this equation yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8 minus 0.32 a equals b\"><mn>8</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0.32</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>